The paper deals with the development of a novel deep reinforcement learning framework for one-shot learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also discusses the application of this framework in computer vision and intrusion detection tasks, which are subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of the framework in computer vision tasks, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision), and the development of a deep-Q network, which is a subfield of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
